headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 36 points, Chris Paul added 18 points and 10 assists and the rising Phoenix Suns beat the Philadelphia 76ers 120-111 on Saturday for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns keep rolling, top 76ers 120-111 for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Doug McDermott scored 26 points, Myles Turner had 19 points and 10 rebounds, and the Indiana Pacers won their second straight game with a 125-113 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDermott, Turner spark Pacers past struggling Hawks

events.name: Houston Rockets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle and rookie Immanuel Quickley each scored 22 points and the New York Knicks sent the Houston Rockets to a season-high fifth straight loss with a 121-99 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks send Rockets to fifth straight loss with 121-99 win

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant won his long-anticipated first trip back to the Bay Arena to play the Warriors team he helped capture two titles over three years, scoring 20 points in the Brooklyn Nets' 134-117 victory over Golden State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant leads Brooklyn past Warriors in Golden State reunion

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points to lead the Utah Jazz to their seventh consecutive victory, 112-94 over the Miami Heat on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Heat 112-94 for seventh straight victory
